args: I just don't know... No matter what\nI try, it seems to get me nowhere.

I've scanned my body from head to toe
and come up with nothing except some
creaky joints that need oiling! Could that
dream just be some kind of delusion?
I'm sure Eirene could clear this up for me\nif I asked her directly, but for some reason,\nI...I just can't.
Finni, you have been acting conspicuously\nunusual for some time. Do you perhaps\nrequire maintenance?
Huh? Oh, Laxi. Don't worry.\nIt has nothing to do with you.
If there are any anomalies diminishing\nyour performance, you must address them.
▷Is something worrying you? If we\ncan help, please just say the word.◁

I told you, it's none of your business.
...Actually, I suppose since I've left Ex
Machina, there isn't anyone else I can
ask about android-related matters.
Okay, fine. I guess asking you can't hurt.
▷A...dream?◁\nIrrational. We androids don't sleep,\nso we can't dream.
Cool, thanks. Great talk. I should've\nknown you'd shut me down.\nNow I'm just annoyed.
▷Come on, Laxi. It might not sound\nrealistic, but there's no point in denying\nthat something's happening to her.◁

▷These ＂dreams＂ could be involuntary 
recollections of unfamiliar memories.
There's no reason to think that
couldn't happen to us as well.◁

That's exactly it. The thing is, the
memories are totally foreign to me.
It's not like they were previously erased;
I genuinely never had them to begin with.

▷How can that be?◁ This grows more
and more incomprehensible.
I can only conclude that the cause
is your damaged heart.

▷The heart does bring together and
coordinate a variety of different functions.
The damage to your heart COULD have
made some memories inaccessible.◁
Then what am I supposed to do about it?\nIt's not like our hearts can be repaired.
A strong shock should do the trick.\nWhen my heart was damaged, it made\nme remember a bit about Maestro.
Hm. So I just need to jolt the memories\nout of stasis, basically?

It's possible that it could temporarily
restore your heart's dormant functions.
▷I-is it just me, or does this plan sound
a little more violent than necessary?◁
Hey, the proof is in the punching!\nOne shock to the system, coming right up!
Let's go the electric route first. We'll force\na short-circuit and zap the memories outta\nwhatever hole they're hiding in!
▷This is absurd! If this goes wrong, you\nmight be lucky to hold on to the memories\nyou have now. Finni, are you okay?!◁
*cough* Well, I'm feeling nice and tingly\nfrom the shock, but that's about it.\nDammit. On to Plan B!

If at first you don't shock-ceed, then fire,
fire again! We'll try to overheat my internal
systems by hitting me with a blast
almost hot enough to melt my armor!

Your internal cooling systems can mitigate
this level of heat. This is entirely pointless
unless you expose yourself to a degree hot
enough to melt down your entire body.
Huh. Okay, yeah, even I can see the risk\nin that. Guess we'll try something else.

Oookay then, we'll just use some good
old-fashioned physics and RATTLE my
heart by giving it a good thwack.
Laxi, smack me as hard as you can!

▷What?! You can't do that!
That's such a violent metho—◁
Understood. I will deliver a powerful but
non-lethal impact to your heart.
OOOPH!\nThat should definitely do the trick...
*sigh* It hasn't jogged my memory in the\nslightest. Dammit! Did we blow it again?!
*pant* *pant* We've tried so many\nthings and have nothing to show for it.
A fruitless effort. I conclude that\nthis day was spent utterly in vain.
Sadly, I think you're right. Bah. For having\na damaged heart, my body sure is sturdy.
▷You say that like it's a bad thing. I really\ndo understand how you feel, but I think we\nought to give it a rest for now, Finni.◁
Say, Laxi? Eirene can read other\nandroids' memories. What about you?
I have never attempted it, so I don't know.\nThat being said, I can attempt to do so.\n▷Finni... You can't mean...◁
I do. Read my memories. I can't go on\nwondering if Eirene is hiding something\nfrom me.
▷Are you sure about this? Even if it\nmeans we'll be probing into your past?◁
I'm not exactly thrilled by the idea,\nbut we're out of options.\nPlease, just do it.
Very well. Commencing with intent\nto procure targeted memories.
Ngh... I-it burns! My heart is getting so\nhot it feels like it's going to explode!
(From the second I started dreaming,\nI knew without a doubt that this dream\nwas different from the others.)
Finni! Finni! No! NO! Don't leave me!
(Recollection after recollection\nbegan flooding into my mind.)
(Everything about the me who wasn't me.\nAnd everything about the day she met her\nend.)
What...? Finni's heart is shining.\nIt's so badly damaged, but if it's\nreacting like this, then it must still be...
If I transplant it into one of those general\nsoldier-type models there, perhaps she\nmight start functioning again.

All of them have been laid to waste by
the Other...but all I need is one. Just one
whose body is in at least somewhat decent
condition...
There! Okay, Finni. I'm going to transplant\nyour heart into this body.
So please...come back to me, my partner.
Was that from a thousand years ago?
That was the day I...\nNo, the day SHE was destroyed.
She was a leader unit—an android\nbuilt more than a thousand years ago.
In the war with Morsayati, she was\nseriously damaged, but Eirene couldn't\naccept it.

That's when Eirene made a choice.
She extracted the heart, which had
somehow survived, and transplanted it
into a mass-produced android body.
But it didn't quite work. When the\nandroid rebooted, it lost its original\nmemories, and its personality changed.
Tell me, Laxi. Mascula. Do you think\nI've always been a substitute for her?
The calm and logical leader unit Finni, I\nmean. Do you think Eirene looks after me\nbecause she misses the Finni I used to be?
I can't say one way or the other.\nOnly she knows the answer to that.
I can't see how it could be anything else.\nWhen she transplanted the heart, Eirene\nwas desperate.
Eirene wanted the other me to come\nback to her. And that means I've royally\nscrewed up in a way I can never unscrew.
I couldn't even conceive the first thing\nabout how she felt. All this time, I've\nbeen such a thoughtless idiot.
Where do I even begin to make amends...?
